Name: Potion
Description: Restores a small amount of health.

Name: Mega Potion
Description:
Restores a moderate amount
of health.

Name: Antidote
Description: A cure for poison.

Name: Max Potion
Description:
Fully restores health and
temporarily maximizes the
size of your Health Gauge.

Name: Ancient Potion
Description:
Fully restores health and
temporarily maximizes the size of
your Health and Stamina Gauges.

Name: Nulberry
Description:
A mysterious berry that cures various
blights.

Name: Ration
Description:
Food that restores a bit of stamina.
It can also be used on the Portable
BBQ Grill to have a meal.

Name: Well-done Steak
Description:
A hearty roast that restores health
and stamina and boosts both their
max gauges. So tasty!

Name: Rare Steak
Description:
Restores health and stamina and
moderately increases the size
of your Health Gauge temporarily.

Name: Burnt Meat
Description:
Restores stamina, but it may
be a bit too charred to provide
any healing effects...

Name: Lifepowder
Description:
Produces a cloud that heals
you and anyone nearby.

Name: Raw Meat
Description:
Meat carved from a monster.
Can be cooked, combined, 
or used to set a trap.

Name: Barrel Bomb
Description: A small time bomb.

Name: Large Barrel Bomb
Description:
A bomb that can be rolled after
placing it on the ground. Strike
it to trigger a powerful blast.

Name: Flash Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that causes a violent
flash on impact. Will temporarily blind
monsters if used in front of them.

Name: Stone
Description:
Slinger ammo that can be used to
hit faraway plant life and bombs.

Name: Capture Net
Description:
A net that can be fired from your
Slinger. Use it to capture small
creatures.

Name: Pitfall Trap
Description:
A trap for catching large monsters.
It is tripped by heavy weight.

Name: Shock Trap
Description:
A trap that immobilizes a target.
Use it to capture monsters.

Name: Whetstone
Description:
A standard-sized whetstone. Use it
to restore a weapon's sharpness.

Name: Binoculars
Description:
A tool that magnifies distant
objects and lets you learn more
about them.

Name: Camping Kit
Description:
A kit with all the tools to make
camp. Use to set up and edit Pop-up
Camps in available campsites.

Name: Portable BBQ Grill
Description:
A portable BBQ grill that can be
used for grilling up raw meat and
other ingredients.

Name: Herb
Description: A primary ingredient in potions.

Name: Antidote Herb
Description:
A primary ingredient in
antidotes.

Name: Honey
Description:
Highly nutritious honey.
Combine with potions to make
the more potent mega potion.

Name: Bitterbug Broth
Description:
Bitterbug essence that has
innate healing abilities. Used as
a component in many medicines.

Name: Flashbug Phosphor
Description:
Luminous essence from an insect
that emits a powerful flash when
it dies. Used to craft flash pods.

Name: Godbug Essence
Description:
Essence from an insect said to
live a millennium. Combine it with
other items to add their properties.

Name: Thunderbug Capacitor
Description:
Substance from an insect that emits
electricity when struck. Required to
craft Shock Traps and Thunder Ammo.

Name: Doshaguma Hide
Description:
A Doshaguma hide. The numerous
scars on its body are proof of
its beastly, aggressive nature.

Name: Doshaguma Fur
Description:
Doshaguma fur. It makes a durable
crafting material thanks to its
stiff, bristly texture.

Name: Doshaguma Claw
Description:
A Doshaguma claw. Sharp as it is
tough, it can cut through muscled
prey without a single chip.

Name: Doshaguma Fang
Description:
A Doshaguma fang. They grow
large and sharp so they can
pierce their prey with ease.

Name: Beast Gem
Description:
A valuable jewel formed from
coagulated juices inside a
monster. Glows wildly.

Name: Normal Ammo
Description:
Standard ammo. Fires multiple
shots with each pull of the trigger.
Unlimited capacity.

Name: Pierce Ammo
Description:
Armor-piercing ammo. Depending
on the monster, it can deal multiple
hits. Unlimited capacity.

Name: Spread Ammo
Description:
Ammo made for close combat.
Short range but high power.
Unlimited capacity.

Name: Sticky Ammo
Description:
Powerful ammo that lodges
in a target and explodes.
Headshots stun.

Name: Cluster Bomb
Description:
Ammo that fragments into
multiple shells upon impact.
Beware of friendly fire!

Name: Flaming Ammo
Description:
Ammo that packs a punch
against monsters susceptible
to fire.

Name: Water Ammo
Description:
Ammo that packs a punch
against monsters susceptible
to water.

Name: Thunder Ammo
Description:
Ammo that packs a punch
against monsters susceptible
to thunder.

Name: Freeze Ammo
Description:
Ammo that packs a punch
against monsters susceptible
to ice.

Name: Dragon Ammo
Description:
Ammo that packs a punch
against monsters weak to
dragon.

Name: Poison Ammo
Description:
Ammo that inflicts poison. Some
targets require multiple shots in
order for the status to take effect.

Name: Paralysis Ammo
Description:
Ammo that causes paralysis. Some
targets require multiple shots in
order for the status to take effect.

Name: Sleep Ammo
Description:
Ammo that induces sleep. Some
targets require multiple shots in
order for the status to take effect.

Name: Slicing Ammo
Description:
Ammo that ejects sharp blades
on impact, which can sever tails.

Name: Thorngrass Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that lodges into
a target. Attacking where it's
lodged deals extra damage.

Name: Iron Ore
Description:
Ore that can be smelted into a
multi-purpose metal.

Name: Machalite Ore
Description:
Ore mined from mineral veins.
Refined Machalite Steel is far
sturdier than its iron cousin.

Name: Dragonite Ore
Description:
Ore sourced from mining outcrops.
A rare material coveted for its
durability in armor crafting.

Name: Carbalite Ore
Description:
Ore obtained from mining outcrops.
Still under research, but known to
yield highly pure metal.

Name: Earth Crystal
Description:
Crystallized microbes sourced from
mining outcrops. Coveted as an
abrasive for polishing equipment.

Name: Mystery Bone
Description:
A weathered bone taken from
a bonepile. Erosion has left it
too fragile to use in crafting.

Name: Sturdy Bone
Description:
A rigid bone taken from
a bonepile. Durable but
light and easy to handle.

Name: Brute Bone
Description:
A sturdy bone from a beast.
Easy to use in crafting.

Name: Colossal Bone
Description:
A massive bone from a beast.
Carefully cut out and used
for crafting.

Name: Dragonbone Relic
Description:
A high-quality bone taken from a
bonepile. The remains of a dragon
that once roamed these lands.

Name: Mandragora
Description:
A dangerous fungus said to draw
the life out of people. Required to
craft immunizers and max potions.

Name: Blue Mushroom
Description:
A mushroom infused with
power-enhancing effects.
Used in restorative items.

Name: Burst Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that detonates on
impact. Use it to stagger a monster
when you're in a pinch.

Name: Screamer Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that emits a harsh,
high-frequency sound that can
disrupt sensitive monsters.

Name: Bleeding Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that can be used
to inflict massive damage on
monster wounds.

Name: Dung Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that releases a
strong odor on impact. Causes
certain monsters to flee.

Name: Trap Tool
Description:
A must-have item for putting
together pitfall traps and
shock traps.

Name: Exciteshroom
Description:
Has a very strange aroma.
Is it edible? Is it deadly?
Required to make farcasters.

Name: Smokenut
Description:
A nut that produces torrents of
smoke. Combine with other items
to add more effects.

Name: Ivy
Description:
A lightweight and extremely
strong plant. Used to make
nets for pitfall traps.

Name: Farcaster
Description:
Call for a wingdrake to transport
you to the nearest camp. Can
also be used during combat.

Name: Balahara Shell
Description:
A Balahara shell. The
fulgurite it has absorbed
enhances its hardness.

Name: Balahara Scale
Description:
A Balahara scale. The erosion
caused by constant digging limits
its usefulness in crafting.

Name: Balahara Skull
Description:
The skull of a Balahara.
Stronger than most, it's built to
withstand harsh dives into sand.

Name: Balahara Tail
Description:
A Balahara tail. Its unique, twisted
shape allows it to propel itself
through earth with great force.

Name: Chatacabra Jaw
Description:
The mandible plating of a
Chatacabra. Hard protrusions
stud the thick but supple leather.

Name: Chatacabra Hide
Description:
The thick hide of a Chatacabra.
Elastic and easy to mold thanks to
the monster's gluttonous diet.

Name: Chatacabra Shell
Description:
Plating that covers a Chatacabra's
forelimbs. A lifetime of licking has
left it both smooth and sturdy.

Name: Chatacabra Scale
Description:
A jagged scale from a Chatacabra's
hide, especially tough and well
suited for use in crafting armor.

Name: Quematrice Scale
Description:
The scale of a Quematrice. Its
fine texture acts as a natural file
used to grind and polish armor.

Name: Quematrice Hide
Description:
The hide of a Quematrice. Quite
thick despite its wrinkly form,
it is highly resistant to fire.

Name: Quematrice Crest
Description:
The crest of a Quematrice. Its
flamboyant red color serves as
a decoy to would-be predators.

Name: Quematrice Tail
Description:
The tail of a Quematrice. Its
many pleats scrape against
each other to create sparks.

Name: Wyvern Gem
Description:
Throughout a wyvern's life,
impurities gather and form
this peculiar gem.

Name: Herbivore Shell
Description:
Part of a shell taken from an
herbivore. Relatively sturdy for
a small monster material.

Name: Bulaqchi Shell
Description:
A Bulaqchi shell. Great for
crafting thanks to its advanced
durability and light weight.

Name: Talioth Scale
Description:
A Talioth scale. Conditioned in
harsh environments, it is built
to protect the body like armor.

Name: Sharp Fang
Description:
Fangs come in many shapes
and sizes. Choose the right
fang for the job.

Name: Wingdrake Hide
Description:
A material carved from
wingdrakes. Lightweight and
often used when crafting armor.

Name: Acute Fang
Description:
Fangs come in many shapes
and sizes. This one is small
but can still pierce scale.

Name: Dung
Description:
Its eye-watering stench makes
useful Slinger ammo.

Name: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_100
Description: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_EXP_100

Name: Rolled-up Dung
Description:
A ball of condensed monster
dung. Used to make dung pods
for your Slinger.

Name: Rathian Scale+
Description:
A superior Rathian scale.
Looks like a normal Rathian
scale but is much harder.

Name: Rathian Carapace
Description:
Rathian carapace prized for
its lavish green coloration.
An excellent armor material.

Name: Rathian Webbing
Description:
A quality Rathian wing membrane.
This heat-resistant material is
often used as armor lining.

Name: Rathian Spike+
Description:
Rathian hairs, keen as a sword.
Longer and sturdier than normal,
they also contain more poison.

Name: Rathian Ruby
Description:
A rare, precious gem from inside
a Rathian. Almost too nice to use.

Name: Toadstool
Description:
A mushroom with poison
properties. Needed to craft
Poison Ammo and smoke bombs.

Name: Parashroom
Description:
A mushroom that induces paralysis.
Needed to craft Paralysis Ammo
and tranq bombs.

Name: Sleep Herb
Description:
A plant containing sleeping
agents. Needed to craft Sleep
Ammo and tranq bombs.

Name: Fire Herb
Description:
A wondrous, flammable plant.
Useful for crafting explosives
and Flaming Ammo.

Name: Flowfern
Description:
This plant's leaves store a great
amount of water. A component
for making Water Ammo.

Name: Snow Herb
Description:
A plant that radiates ice-cold
air. Use in combinations to
create Freeze Ammo.

Name: Dragonfell Berry
Description:
A mysterious berry rumored for
eons to be loathed by dragons.
Required to craft Dragon Ammo.

Name: First-aid Med
Description:
Restores a small amount of health.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Ration
Description:
Restores a small amount of stamina.
Not usable with Portable BBQ Grill.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Flash Bomb
Description:
Slinger ammo that explodes
with a bright flash after it's fired.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Shock Trap
Description:
A trap that immobilizes a target.
Use it to capture monsters.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Pitfall Trap
Description:
Activates a pitfall to catch
monsters with.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: Gloamgrass Bud
Description:
A plant with healing properties.
Combine with Godbug essence
to unleash its true potential.

Name: Might Seed
Description:
Temporarily strengthens your
attacks when ingested by
improving energy flow.

Name: Adamant Seed
Description:
Temporarily raises your
defense when ingested by
hardening tissue.

Name: Nitroshroom
Description:
A hard-to-find mushroom with the
power to generate blazing heat.
Required to craft gunpowder.

Name: Devil's Blight
Description:
A very rare fungus that pulses with
extreme heat. Add to a barrel bomb
for a dramatically stronger blast.

Name: Blastnut
Description:
A nut that explodes its hard
contents on impact. Used to
make Sticky Ammo.

Name: Slashberry
Description:
A berry that shatters into
razor-like pieces. Used
to make Slicing Ammo.

Name: Rey Dau Scale
Description:
A Rey Dau scale. Its unique
shape allows electricity from
its organs to pass through.

Name: Rey Dau Shell
Description:
The shell from a Rey Dau.
Highly conductive and capable of
producing large electrical currents.

Name: Rey Dau Thunderhorn
Description:
An electrically charged Rey Dau
horn. The thick, flexible muscle
at its base lets it move freely.

Name: Rey Dau Wingtalon
Description:
The claw-shaped energy conduit of
a Rey Dau. Coated in sharp fulgurite
blades formed by electric discharges.

Name: Rey Dau Tail
Description:
A Rey Dau tail. Its fulgurite-
covered spines rub together to
produce a threatening melody.

Name: Rey Dau Plate
Description:
A Rey Dau plate. The backward-
facing scale accumulates
a massive amount of energy.

Name: Tranq Blade
Description:
A knife coated with a tranquilizer
that can be shot from your Slinger
to put trapped monsters to sleep.

Name: Poison Knife
Description:
A knife fired with the Slinger,
inflicting poison on a target.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: Paralysis Knife
Description:
A knife fired with the Slinger,
inflicting paralysis on a target.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: Sleep Knife
Description:
A knife fired with the Slinger,
inflicting sleep on a target.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: Smoke Bomb
Description:
Creates a large cloud of smoke when
thrown against the ground that can
hide you from a monster's sight.

Name: Powercharm
Description:
An amulet that strengthens
attacks. Just carrying this
gives you demonic strength.

Name: Armorcharm
Description:
An amulet that increases
defense. Just carrying this
makes your skin stone hard.

Name: Wyvern Ammo
Description:
Ammo created through years
of research into Wyvern's Fire.
Short ranged, but destructive.

Name: Grounding Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that can dissipate
electricity from the area it lands.

Name: Mystery Orb - Armor
Description:
A sphere with faint power that
is revealed through appraisal.
Becomes a defensive decoration.

Name: Glowing Orb - Armor
Description:
A sphere with hidden power that
is revealed through appraisal.
Becomes a defensive decoration.

Name: Ancient Orb - Armor
Description:
A sphere with incredible power that
is revealed through appraisal.
Becomes a defensive decoration.

Name: Damaged Weapon Shard
Description:
An old, damaged weapon part.
Needs to be appraised.

Name: Rusted Weapon Shard
Description:
An old, rusted weapon part.
Needs to be appraised.

Name: Ghillie Mantle
Description:
Temporarily conceal yourself
from view. The effect ends if you
perform an attack or take damage.

Name: Fishing Rod
Description:
A tool for fishing. Cast the
lure into bodies of water and
use the reel to wind in the line.

Name: Energy Drink
Description:
A Guild-approved beverage
that boosts your stamina.
Helps shake off sleep, too!

Name: Dash Juice
Description:
Recovers stamina and also temporarily
reduces stamina depletion when
performing actions.

Name: Immunizer
Description:
Temporarily boosts your natural
ability to recover lost health.

Name: Cool Drink
Description:
Provides temporary relief
from extreme heat.

Name: Hot Drink
Description:
Provides temporary relief
from extreme cold.

Name: Demondrug
Description:
Temporarily boosts your
attack power by filling
you with demonic strength.

Name: Might Pill
Description:
Temporarily endows you with
the strength of a mighty god.
Potent!

Name: Mega Demondrug
Description:
Temporarily boosts your
attack power even more
than a regular Demondrug.

Name: Armorskin
Description:
Temporarily boosts your
defense by turning your
skin as hard as rock.

Name: Adamant Pill
Description:
Temporarily makes your skin
as hard as adamant. Potent!

Name: Mega Armorskin
Description:
Temporarily boosts your
defense even more than
regular Armorskin.

Name: Herbal Medicine
Description:
Removes all traces of poison
and restores a slight amount
of health.

Name: Herbal Powder
Description:
Produces a cloud that cures
poison and heals you a bit.

Name: Demon Powder
Description:
A mysterious powder that produces
a cloud around the area that
temporarily strengthens attacks.

Name: Hardshell Powder
Description:
A mysterious powder; when
dispersed, temporarily
strengthens defense.

Name: Dust of Life
Description:
Produces a cloud that restores
a large amount of health for you
and anyone nearby.

Name: Cleanser
Description:
Immediately removes any frost
or webbing on your body.

Name: Poison Smoke Bomb
Description:
Releases a cloud of toxic
mist when used. Also popular
as a household bug bomb.

Name: Tranq Bomb
Description:
A hand grenade used to capture
monsters ensnared in traps. Can
be slammed against the ground.

Name: Throwing Knife
Description:
A knife that can be equipped to
your Slinger. Can be coated with
a range of substances.

Name: Poison Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that inflicts 
poison on a target upon 
impact.

Name: Para Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that inflicts
paralysis on a target upon
impact.

Name: Drugged Meat
Description:
Raw meat that puts whatever
eats it to sleep. Makes
great bait for traps.

Name: Brightmoss
Description:
Slinger ammo that illuminates
dark areas when fired and can
dazzle flying monsters.

Name: Torch Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that can be used
to scare away creatures that don't
like fire and draw in those that do.

Name: Puddle Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo imbued with water
element. Can remove some statuses
on monsters.

Name: Bomb Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that explodes
on impact.

Name: Piercing Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that deals piercing
damage on impact.

Name: Paint Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that makes a
monster or location temporarily
easier to find.

Name: Luring Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that can be used
to lure monsters toward yourself.

Name: Mega Barrel Bomb
Description:
An upgraded large barrel bomb.
Effective against large monsters.
Can be rolled after placement.

Name: First-aid Med+
Description:
Restores a moderate amount
of health. Returned after
quest completion.

Name: EZ Max Potion
Description:
Fully restores health and maximizes
the size of your Health Gauge.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Lifepowder
Description:
Produces a cloud that heals
you and anyone nearby.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Herbal Powder
Description:
Cures poison and restores a bit
of health for everyone nearby.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Demon Powder
Description:
Temporarily strengthens attacks
for everyone nearby. Returned
after quest completion.

Name: EZ Hardshell Powder
Description:
Temporarily increases defense
for everyone nearby. Returned
after quest completion.

Name: EZ Dust of Life
Description:
Releases a cloud that restores a
large amount of health. Returned
after quest completion.

Name: EZ Tranq Bomb
Description:
A hand grenade used to capture
monsters ensnared in traps.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Dung Pod
Description:
Releases a strong odor on impact.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Sonic Bomb
Description:
Slinger ammo that emits an
earsplitting sonic blast.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: Tinged Meat
Description:
Raw meat that paralyzes whatever
eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

Name: EZ Large Barrel Bomb
Description:
An improved large barrel bomb.
Can be rolled after being placed.
Returned after quest completion.

Name: EZ Farcaster
Description:
Call for a wingdrake to transport
you to the nearest camp. Returned
after quest completion.

Name: Poisoned Meat
Description:
Raw meat that poisons whatever
eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

Name: Deodorant
Description:
Produces a cloud of cleansing
smoke that cures blastblight
and stench.

Name: Kunafa Cheese
Description:
An artisan cheese made in Kunafa,
deliciously gooey when heated,
and a great addition to any dish.

Name: Sharp Kunafa Cheese
Description:
A rich, decadent cheese made
by skilled craftspeople. A great
addition to any dish.

Name: Droolshroom
Description:
A mushroom that grows in a secret
spot known only to Wudwuds.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Delishroom
Description:
An extremely rare delicacy that is
cause for a Wudwud celebration.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Mud Shrimp
Description:
A nutritious shrimp native to
Oilwell Basin and favored in Azuz.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Turbid Shrimp
Description:
A large, chewy shrimp packed
to the gills with nutrients.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Fluffy Egg
Description:
An egg with a yolk and white as
fluffy as the Downy Crake that
laid it. A great addition to any dish.

Name: Airy Egg
Description:
A high-quality egg that sends
you straight to flavor heaven.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Sild Garlic
Description:
A highly nutritious and fragrant
bulb of garlic grown in Sild.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Specialty Sild Garlic
Description:
The ultimate bulb of garlic, grown
in just the right conditions.
A great addition to any dish.

Name: Wild Herb
Description:
This herb's refreshing aroma can
mask any foul odor. A great
finishing touch to any dish.

Name: Eastern Honey
Description:
Has a unique flavor, making it the
perfect secret ingredient. A great
finishing touch to any dish.

Name: Monster Chili
Description:
A powerful spice that enhances
flavor and sweat production. A
great finishing touch to any dish.

Name: Jeweled Mullet Roe
Description:
These fish eggs truly shine
like diamonds. A great
finishing touch to any dish.

Name: Wild Seed Oil
Description:
Oil that packs both flavor and
the power of nature. A great
finishing touch to any dish.

Name: Truffle Du Conga
Description:
Often dug up by its namesake,
Congalala. A great finishing
touch to any dish.

Name: Sinister Cloth
Description:
Suspicious cloth found somewhere
in the Windward Plains. Drips with
an aura of pure evil.

Name: Great Hornfly
Description:
Found in the Scarlet Forest.
An insect with a giant horn,
huge shell, and butterfly wings.

Name: Windward Aloe
Description:
Found in the Windward Plains. The
water stored within its plump leaves
has saved many a parched traveler.

Name: Fine Windward Aloe
Description:
A rarity from the Windward Plains.
A single drop of its delicious sap
transforms water into ambrosia.

Name: Great Windward Aloe
Description:
A treasure of the Windward Plains.
Its leaves hold enough water to
fill a bath in the driest desert.

Name: Sandpepper
Description:
Found in the Windward Plains.
This dried spice lends a rich and
aromatic heat to any dish.

Name: Fiery Sandpepper
Description:
A rarity from the Windward Plains.
A spice so hot that a single bite
opens the taster's third eye.

Name: Fulgurite Shard
Description:
Found in the Windward Plains.
The shape of this fulgurite was
sculpted by a chance lightning strike.

Name: Pure Fulgurite
Description:
A rarity from the Windward Plains.
Crystallized fulgurite, free of any
impurity. Extremely delicate.

Name: Thundering Fulgurite
Description:
A treasure of the Windward Plains.
A colossal fulgurite crystal, born
of a sky-splitting thunderstrike.

Name: Scarlet Amber Shard
Description:
Amber from the Scarlet Forest.
The bodies of fossilized insects
float in its scarlet confines.

Name: Fine Scarlet Amber
Description:
Rare amber from the Scarlet Forest.
Immaculate insect specimens sleep
in this amber, red as fine liquor.

Name: Eternal Scarlet Amber
Description:
Colossal amber from the Scarlet
Forest. Ancient life has been
sealed away inside it for eons.

Name: Queensbloom Pollen
Description:
Pollen from a giant flower in the
Scarlet Forest, as regal as it is
massive. Makes a heady perfume.

Name: Shiny Treasure
Description:
An ancient artifact Wudwuds
found in the Scarlet Forest.
Purely aesthetic in nature.

Name: Sparkly Treasure
Description:
A rarity of the Scarlet Forest. The
fine detail and lavish use of gold
show quite advanced techniques.

Name: Bulky Treasure
Description:
The sheer scale of this Scarlet
Forest rarity makes it the object
of obsession for all Wudwuds.

Name: Auric Oil
Description:
Exceptionally pure, golden
mineral oil from Oilwell Basin.
Used widely in Flameborn crafts.

Name: Antimite
Description:
A mineral from Oilwell Basin
with a unique sheen. Used by the
Flameborn in alloy production.

Name: Fine Antimite
Description:
An Oilwell Basin rarity too pure
to be worked by any but the
Flameborn artisans.

Name: Antimite Mass
Description:
A hulking antimite formation that
produces strange reactions not yet
understood by science.

Name: Hirabami Molting
Description:
Skin shed from a Hirabami.
Treasured by the people of the
Iceshard Cliffs as a curative.

Name: Wyvernscale Vase
Description:
An ancient ornamental vase found
in the Iceshard Cliffs. The techniques
used to craft it are lost to time.

Name: Dragonscale Vase
Description:
Each individual scale ornamenting
this vase from the Iceshard Cliffs
sparkles with a fiery brilliance.

Name: Large Goldenscale Vase
Description:
An exquisite, inscribed vase from
the Iceshard Cliffs. A treasure
worthy of kings, lost to the world.

Name: Wyveria Lantern
Description:
Fruit encased in a mesh shell, found
in the Ruins of Wyveria. A precious
source of sustenance to the natives.

Name: Mature Wyveria Lantern
Description:
A rarity in the Ruins of Wyveria.
The ripening process imbues the
fruit with medicinal properties.

Name: Origin Wylk Gem
Description:
A precious find from the Ruins of
Wyveria. More transparent than other
Wylkdrops and has considerable heft.

Name: Milky Cocoon Web
Description:
A curious fiber found in the Ruins
of Wyveria. A resource treasured
by the Keepers.

Name: Wylk Pebble
Description:
Small stones found across the East.
A rich source of energy, they are
often burned for fuel.

Name: Wylk Gem
Description:
A beautiful, faintly luminescent
stone occasionally found inside
Wylkdrops harvested in the East.

Name: Time-honed Wylk Gem
Description:
The size of this rare find from
the East is the result of an eons-
long natural formation process.

Name: Ancient Fossil
Description:
The blackened, stony remains of old
bones unearthed in the East. When
polished, it gains a velvety sheen.

Name: Drifting Sea Pot
Description:
A species of translucent sea squirts
found in the East. When salt-dried,
it becomes a fine preserved food.

Name: Royal Sea Pot
Description:
A rare, meatier species of sea
squirt found in the East. Keeps
its rich flavor, even when preserved.

Name: Gobletweed
Description:
Algae that grows in the East.
It resembles a ceremonial cup—
Cheers for finding such a beauty!

Name: Chaliceweed
Description:
Care must be taken not to disturb
the delicate form of this rare and
stunning algae when harvesting it.

Name: Nightflower Pollen
Description:
Pollen from a flower that
blooms under a full moon. It
exudes an ethereal pale glow.

Name: Fossilized Opal
Description:
A mass of organic material
fossilized into opal over time.
It has a deep crimson shine.

Name: Fossilized Fire Opal
Description:
This gorgeous fossil is marked by
an exceptionally clear and fiery
opal. A truly radiant rarity.

Name: Genesis Opal
Description:
The opal inclusion in this fossil
burns with the fire of creation
that first shaped this world.

Name: Wyvernsprout
Description:
A parasitic fungus that grows on
the bodies of dead monsters. Prized
as a symbol of reincarnation.

Name: Whetfish Fin
Description:
A fish fin that greatly restores
sharpness and requires fewer
strokes than a whetstone.

Name: Sushifish Scale
Description:
A scale from a Sushifish.
Slightly restores health
and treats bleeding.

Name: Lala Barina Shell
Description:
The outer shell of a Lala
Barina. Has a dark luster and
is wonderfully lightweight.

Name: Lala Barina Claw
Description:
A claw from a Lala Barina. Vivid
scarlet decorates its keen edge.

Name: Lala Barina Stinger
Description:
The stinger from a Lala Barina.
Sharp as a sword, one thrust
is all it takes to subdue prey.

Name: Lala Barina Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Lala
Barina. Used to make equipment.

Name: Lala Barina Floret
Description:
Hair from a Lala Barina. So
white and pristine that it could
pass for a high quality pelt.

Name: Screamer Pod
Description:
Used as ammo for your Slinger. Emits
a harsh, high-frequency sound that
can disrupt sensitive monsters.

Name: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_280
Description: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_EXP_280

Name: Krano Copper
Description:
Copper pyrite from a Kranodath's
shell. Its luster makes it a prime
material for decorations.

Name: Krano Pyrite
Description:
High-quality copper pyrite from
a Kranodath's shell. Its brilliant
sheen is stunning to behold.

Name: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_283
Description: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_EXP_283

Name: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_284
Description: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_EXP_284

Name: Thunder Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo imbued with thunder
element.

Name: Frost Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo imbued with ice
element.

Name: Dragon Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo imbued with dragon
element.

Name: Fresh Honey
Description:
Special honey gathered from
Y'sai's spot. Can be delivered to
Provisions, who's running low.

Name: Frostburst
Description:
Slinger ammo imbued with the ice
element. Use it to stagger a
monster when you're in a pinch.

Name: Dragonstrike Nut
Description:
A nut that explodes on
impact. Used to make
Wyvern Ammo.

Name: Bomberry
Description:
A berry that ruptures on impact.
Used to make cluster bombs.

Name: Chatacabra Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Chatacabra.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Chatacabra Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Chatacabra scale.
Its enhanced durability makes
it impervious to most blows.

Name: Chatacabra Jaw+
Description:
Fine plating from a Chatacabra's
hulking jaw. Its density and heft
are quite impressive.

Name: Chatacabra Hide+
Description:
A high-quality Chatacabra hide.
Tempered by its harsh environment.
Makes a fine crafting material.

Name: Chatacabra Carapace
Description:
Stout plating from a Chatacabra's
arms. Constant friction with the
ground has polished it to gleam.

Name: Chatacabra Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Chatacabra.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Xu Wu Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Xu Wu.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Quematrice Igniter
Description:
Flammable fluids from a Quematrice,
expelled as a gas then ignited by
sparks from its coarse tail.

Name: Quematrice Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Quematrice.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Quematrice Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Quematrice scale.
Its keen ridges allow it to cleave
stone in a single stroke.

Name: Quematrice Hide+
Description:
Fine Quematrice hide, hardened by
the struggle to survive. Offers
exceptional fire protection.

Name: Quematrice Igniter+
Description:
Especially viscous fluid from a
Quematrice. The gas it releases
burns at a perilous temperature.

Name: Quematrice Crest+
Description:
The large crest of a Quematrice.
Colored an angry red and shaken
violently in a show of aggression.

Name: Quematrice Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Quematrice.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Lala Barina Floret+
Description:
High-quality hair from a Lala
Barina. Its delicate, transparent
strands dance in the wind.

Name: Lala Barina Carapace
Description:
The hard carapace of a Lala
Barina. A bit of polish will
make it shine black as night.

Name: Lala Barina Claw+
Description:
A sharp claw from a Lala Barina.
The deep crimson tip mirrors
the blood of countless victims.

Name: Lala Barina Stinger+
Description:
The razor-sharp stinger of a Lala
Barina. Capable of piercing even
the thickest armor.

Name: Lala Barina Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Lala
Barina. Used to make equipment.

Name: Balahara Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Balahara.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Balahara Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Balahara scale.
Thick and durable enough to carve
through stone without a scratch.

Name: Balahara Carapace
Description:
A hard Balahara carapace. A
quality material from a specimen
wrapped in pure fulgurite.

Name: Balahara Skull+
Description:
A Balahara's pointy skull. An
incredibly tough shell that digs
through hard bedrock with ease.

Name: Balahara Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Balahara.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Doshaguma Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Doshaguma.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Doshaguma Fur+
Description:
High-quality Doshaguma fur.
So accustomed to harsh climes
that it's akin to armor.

Name: Doshaguma Hide+
Description:
High-quality Doshaguma hide. Its
thick, comfortable weight gives
reassurance to those who wear it.

Name: Doshaguma Claw+
Description:
A sharp Doshaguma claw. One
poke pierces skin, and one
swipe tears flesh from bone.

Name: Doshaguma Fang+
Description:
A sharp Doshaguma fang. Proof
of its owner's feral nature in its
ability to chew through even bone.

Name: Doshaguma Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Doshaguma.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Uth Duna Scale
Description:
A scale from an Uth Duna.
Glistens in a kaleidoscope
of colors.

Name: Uth Duna Hide
Description:
The hide of an Uth Duna. Highly
prized for its density and
spectacularly vibrant pattern.

Name: Uth Duna Cilia
Description:
Extremely fine hair from an Uth
Duna. When woven together, it
forms a thin, watery membrane.

Name: Uth Duna Tentacle
Description:
A tentacle from the back of an
Uth Duna. Covered in a gelatinous
mix of water and body fluid.

Name: Uth Duna Claw
Description:
A claw from an Uth Duna. Its
curvature helps to anchor it
against the waves it creates.

Name: Uth Duna Plate
Description:
A rare plate from an Uth Duna.
Hailed as a symbol of Plenty due
to the amount of water it holds.

Name: Uth Duna Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted an Uth
Duna. Used to make equipment.

Name: Uth Duna Scale+
Description:
A high-quality scale from an Uth
Duna. Thin grooves allow it to
store water to strengthen itself.

Name: Uth Duna Hide+
Description:
A high-quality hide from an
Uth Duna. Its pattern holds
an almost divine beauty.

Name: Uth Duna Cilia+
Description:
High-quality Uth Duna hair. Weak
to cutting force, but can hold
a vast amount of water.

Name: Uth Duna Tentacle+
Description:
An elegant and flexible tentacle
from an Uth Duna. A membrane of
water surrounds it like a veil.

Name: Uth Duna Claw+
Description:
A sharp claw from an Uth Duna.
Heavy enough to easily crush
even the thickest trees.

Name: Uth Duna Watergem
Description:
A rare jewel that developed within
an Uth Duna. Said to wield the
power of a devastating flood.

Name: Uth Duna Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted an Uth
Duna. Used to make equipment.

Name: Rompopolo Hide
Description:
A Rompopolo hide. It returns
to its original shape even
if stretched to its limit.

Name: Rompopolo Claw
Description:
A claw from a Rompopolo.
Developed for the specific
purpose of piercing prey.

Name: Spotted Poison Hide
Description:
A poisonous hide from a Rompopolo.
The vibrant speckles warn of its
inherent danger.

Name: Rompopolo Beak
Description:
The beak of a Rompopolo.
Its disturbing shape evokes an
indescribable sense of unease.

Name: Rompopolo Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Rompopolo.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Rompopolo Hide+
Description:
A high-quality Rompopolo hide.
Can expand to extreme lengths
when filled with gas.

Name: Rompopolo Claw+
Description:
A sharp claw from a Rompopolo.
Perfectly suited to piercing
vitals with acute precision.

Name: Spotted Poison Hide+
Description:
A highly poisonous hide from a
Rompopolo. The more striking the
pattern, the more poisonous it is.

Name: Rompopolo Beak+
Description:
A large beak from a Rompopolo.
Its sharp point and gentle curve
strike untold fear into its prey.

Name: Rompopolo Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Rompopolo.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Rey Dau Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Rey
Dau. Used to make equipment.

Name: Rey Dau Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Rey Dau scale.
Constant exposure to the Sandtide
made it as sturdy as it is smooth.

Name: Rey Dau Carapace
Description:
The tough carapace of a Rey Dau.
Its complex but consistent pattern
enhances its conductivity.

Name: Rey Dau Bolthorn
Description:
A Rey Dau horn crackling with
lightning. Durable enough to
sustain great bolts of electricity.

Name: Rey Dau Fulgurtalon
Description:
A Rey Dau wingtalon with an
azure glow. Coated with pure,
razor-sharp fulgurite.

Name: Rey Dau Boltgem
Description:
A rare jewel that developed
within a Rey Dau. Said to wield
the power of ten thousand storms.

Name: Rey Dau Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Rey
Dau. Used to make equipment.

Name: Hirabami Scale
Description:
A scale from a Hirabami. Though
small and lightweight, it's very
strong and easy to process.

Name: Hirabami Hide
Description:
The hide of a Hirabami. Light
and smooth like cloth, it is
known for its unique texture.

Name: Hirabami Webbing
Description:
Webbing from a Hirabami. Its
superb elasticity allows the
monster to float in the air.

Name: Hirabami Tail Claw
Description:
A claw from the tail of a
Hirabami. Its curved shape
allows it to easily trap prey.

Name: Hirabami Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Hirabami.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Hirabami Scale+
Description:
A high-quality scale from a
Hirabami. Not only is it strong,
but also exceedingly light.

Name: Hirabami Hide+
Description:
A high-quality Hirabami hide.
Soft as the finest fabric, with
the warmth to endure a blizzard.

Name: Hirabami Webbing+
Description:
High-quality Hirabami webbing.
Can manipulate air currents even
in the fiercest blizzards.

Name: Hirabami Tail Claw+
Description:
A high-quality claw from the
tail of a Hirabami. No prey can
escape its scythe-like bite.

Name: Hirabami Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Hirabami.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Ajarakan Scale
Description:
A scale from an Ajarakan. 
Extremely resistant, not even the
hardest of stone will scratch it.

Name: Ajarakan Shell
Description:
The shell of an Ajarakan. Capable
of producing a shower of sparks
with the slightest scrape.

Name: Ajarakan Ridge
Description:
The hard casing that runs along the
back of an Ajarakan. Its bright
scarlet color echoes a raging fire.

Name: Ajarakan Tail
Description:
The tail of an Ajarakan. Its
uneven spikes are highly
combustible.

Name: Ajarakan Jewel
Description:
A rare jewel that developed in
an Ajarakan's body. Said to wield
enough force to explode bedrock.

Name: Ajarakan Marrow
Description:
Bone marrow from an Ajarakan.
Almost too hot to handle.

Name: Ajarakan Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted an Ajarakan.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Ajarakan Scale+
Description:
A high-quality scale from an
Ajarakan. The flame-like spikes
project the monster's hot fury.

Name: Ajarakan Carapace
Description:
A tough Ajarakan carapace.
Even fierce explosions can't
damage it.

Name: Ajarakan Ridge+
Description:
A rock-solid ridge from an
Ajarakan. Reminiscent of a fire
in its color and uneven curves.

Name: Ajarakan Jewel+
Description:
A large jewel that developed
in an Ajarakan. Glows red, as
if holding an inferno within.

Name: Ajarakan Medulla
Description:
The brainstem of an Ajarakan.
Constantly burning, as if all its
body heat is concentrated within.

Name: Ajarakan Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted an Ajarakan.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Nu Udra Hide
Description:
A highly-elastic Nu Udra hide.
It looks smooth but has a subtle
roughness.

Name: Nu Udra Spike
Description:
A Nu Udra spike. Requires
a skilled hand to handle its
twisted, non-uniform shape.

Name: Nu Udra Horn
Description:
A Nu Udra Horn. Curved to
protect the eyes and smattered
with small spines.

Name: Nu Udra Tentacle
Description:
A Nu Udra tentacle. Incredibly
flexible and elastic, only the
sharpest of blades can pierce it.

Name: Nu Udra Oilmucus
Description:
A viscous liquid made from a Nu
Udra's body fluids and oil. Adding
oil to it makes it more flammable.

Name: Nu Udra Cerebrospinal Fluid
Description:
A strange fluid formed inside
a Nu Udra. It glows blue and
can strengthen materials.

Name: Nu Udra Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Nu
Udra. Used to make equipment.

Name: Nu Udra Hide+
Description:
High-quality Nu Udra hide.
Especially elastic and fire
resistant. Eternally slimy.

Name: Nu Udra Spike+
Description:
A quality Nu Udra spike. Will
gouge out the surrounding flesh
when removed from its victim.

Name: Nu Udra Horn+
Description:
A sharp Nu Udra Horn. Each one
twists eerily outward, as if in
search of something.

Name: Nu Udra Tentacle+
Description:
A large Nu Udra tentacle. A huge
slab of muscle that will thrash
uncontrollably even when cut off.

Name: Nu Udra Oilmucus+
Description:
Dense Nu Udra Oilmucus.
Burns unbelievably hot and
long once ignited.

Name: Nu Udra Flamegem
Description:
A mysterious gem formed inside
a Nu Udra. Said to hold the power
to burn the world to the ground.

Name: Nu Udra Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Nu
Udra. Used to make equipment.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Fur
Description:
The fur of a Guardian Doshaguma.
Energy coursing through it has
turned it white and strengthened it.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Hide
Description:
The hide of a Guardian Doshaguma.
It is especially thick and tough,
with a distinctive white pattern.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Claw
Description:
The claw of a Guardian Doshaguma.
Energy coursing through it has
turned it white and rigid.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Fang
Description:
The fang of a Guardian Doshaguma.
Tough enough to withstand the
Doshaguma's fiercely acidic saliva.

Name: G. Doshaguma Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian
Doshaguma. Used to make equipment.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Fur+
Description:
High-quality fur from a Guardian
Doshaguma. Energy coursing through
it has rendered it hard as steel.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Hide+
Description:
A high-quality hide from a Guardian
Doshaguma. Tough as iron and able
to withstand any kind of attack.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Claw+
Description:
An especially sharp claw from a
Guardian Doshaguma. Filled with
energy, it easily cuts through armor.

Name: Guardian Doshaguma Fang+
Description:
An especially sharp fang from a
Guardian Doshaguma. Mercilessly
crushes anything in its way.

Name: G. Doshaguma Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian
Doshaguma. Used to make equipment.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Scale
Description:
A scale from a Guardian Rathalos.
Made thick and tough by the
energy coursing through it.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Shell
Description:
The shell of a Guardian Rathalos.
Still radiates heat from the
energy coursing through it.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Webbing
Description:
Webbing from a Guardian Rathalos.
The energy coursing through it has
enhanced its flight capabilities.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Tail
Description:
The tail of a Guardian Rathalos.
The energy coursing through it has
made it into an adaptable material.

Name: G. Rathalos Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian
Rathalos. Used to make equipment.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Scale+
Description:
A high-quality scale from a
Guardian Rathalos. Accumulated
energy has made it scorching hot.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Carapace
Description:
The tough carapace of a Guardian
Rathalos. Durable enough to
withstand even the fiercest flames.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Wing
Description:
A wing from a Guardian Rathalos.
Energy courses through each vein,
producing gale-force winds.

Name: Equipped Mantles
Description:
The selected mantle in Change
Equipment will be reflected in
your Radial Menu/Loadouts.

Name: G. Rathalos Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian
Rathalos. Used to make equipment.

Name: Rath Medulla
Description:
Only recently extractable due to
advances in carving techniques.
Hard to forge.

Name: Demon Ammo
Description:
Ammo that produces a cloud that
temporarily strengthens attacks
in the impact zone of where it lands.

Name: Armor Ammo
Description:
Ammo that produces a cloud that
temporarily strengthens defense
in the impact zone of where it lands.

Name: Recover Ammo
Description:
Ammo that produces a healing
cloud in the impact zone of
where it lands.

Name: Tranq Ammo
Description:
Ammo used to capture monsters
ensnared in traps.

Name: Exhaust Ammo
Description:
Ammo that drains a monster's
stamina.

Name: Frenzy Shard
Description:
A fragment of a disturbing
crystal that possesses a
hidden power.

Name: Jin Dahaad Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Jin Dahaad scale.
Its metallic properties prevent
it from freezing.

Name: Jin Dahaad Carapace
Description:
The tough carapace of a Jin
Dahaad. Tough as steel without
impeding movement.

Name: Jin Dahaad Iceplate
Description:
From the back of a Jin Dahaad,
this plate's metallic properties allow
it to freeze the surrounding air.

Name: Jin Dahaad Claw+
Description:
A sharp claw from a Jin Dahaad.
Terrifyingly cold, it freezes
everything it touches.

Name: Jin Dahaad Horn
Description:
A layered horn from a Jin Dahaad.
Also acts as a heat vent.

Name: Jin Dahaad Icegem
Description:
A rare jewel developed within
a Jin Dahaad. Said to wield the
power to freeze entire cliffs.

Name: Jin Dahaad Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Jin Dahaad.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Guardian Ebony Scale
Description:
A scale from a Guardian Ebony
Odogaron. Energy coursing through
it has turned parts of it white.

Name: Guardian Ebony Sinew
Description:
Tightly packed sinew from
a Guardian Ebony Odogaron.
Especially strong and heavy.

Name: Guardian Ebony Claw
Description:
A Guardian Ebony Odogaron claw.
Made for ripping things open, even
the slightest touch is dangerous.

Name: Guardian Ebony Fang
Description:
A Guardian Ebony Odogaron fang.
Its sharp point allows it to pierce
the vitals of any prey.

Name: Guardian Ebony Tail
Description:
A Guardian Ebony Odogaron tail.
Covered in bristled scales that
call to mind its terrible rage.

Name: Guardian Ebony Plate
Description:
A Guardian Ebony Odogaron plate.
Energy has bolstered its draconic
power to incredible heights.

Name: G. Ebony Odogaron Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian Ebony
Odogaron. Used to make equipment.

Name: Guardian Ebony Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Guardian Ebony
Odogaron scale. The flow of
pure energy has strengthened it.

Name: Guardian Ebony Sinew+
Description:
A large piece of sinew from a
Guardian Ebony Odogaron. Excess
energy has strengthened it greatly.

Name: Guardian Ebony Claw+
Description:
A sharp claw from a Guardian Ebony
Odogaron. Its saw-like form lets it
mercilessly rip apart its prey.

Name: Guardian Ebony Fang+
Description:
A sharp Guardian Ebony Odogaron
fang. Shrouded in misfortune,
only the bravest dare touch it.

Name: Guardian Ebony Gem
Description:
A rare jewel that developed within
a Guardian Ebony Odogaron. Said
to hold a strange draconic power.

Name: G. Ebony Odogaron Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian Ebony
Odogaron. Used to make equipment.

Name: Nourishing Extract
Description:
Can be obtained from some large
monsters. Has the ability to amplify
the effects of certain medicines.

Name: Xu Wu Hide
Description:
The hide of a Xu Wu. Covered in
mucus and uniquely flexible,
it's quite a trial to work with.

Name: Golden Corneum
Description:
The golden corneum of a Xu Wu.
Formed by hardened secretions that
glisten with a disturbing light.

Name: Xu Wu Tentacle
Description:
A Xu Wu tentacle. It's flexible
musculature makes it perfect for
weapon and armor crafting.

Name: Xu Wu Claw
Description:
A claw from a Xu Wu. Sharp as
a knife and able to pierce prey
without a sound.

Name: Xu Wu Fang
Description:
A fang from a Xu Wu. Tough
enough to crush any matter
of prey.

Name: Xu Wu Cerebrospinal Fluid
Description:
Cerebrospinal fluid from a Xu Wu.
A great deal of energy is concealed
within, causing it to glow.

Name: Xu Wu Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Xu Wu.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Xu Wu Hide+
Description:
A high-quality Xu Wu hide.
Tough enough to repel
a Guardian's claws and fangs.

Name: Golden Corneum+
Description:
A glittering golden corneum of
a Xu Wu. Further hardened by
its extremely pure secretions.

Name: Xu Wu Tentacle+
Description:
A high-quality Xu Wu tentacle.
Continues to squirm while being
processed, displaying its vitality.

Name: Xu Wu Claw+
Description:
A sharp claw from a Xu Wu. It's
longer and keener, allowing it to
more easily bring down prey.

Name: Xu Wu Fang+
Description:
A sharp fang from a Xu Wu. Dyed
with the blood of all the prey it has
mercilessly crushed.

Name: Xu Wu Umbragem
Description:
A rare jewel developed within
a Xu Wu's body. Harbors a deep
and impenetrable darkness.

Name: Guardian Scale
Description:
Contains an unknown substance.
It has lost any color it previously
had and possesses unique properties.

Name: Guardian Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Guardian scale.
Sparkles like snow, as if it had
always been pure white.

Name: Arkveld Tail
Description:
The tail of an Arkveld. Highly prized
for the thick muscle hidden
beneath its skin and hair.

Name: Large Dung Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that releases a
strong odor on impact, causing
any surrounding monsters to flee.

Name: EZ Large Dung Pod
Description:
Releases a foul odor over a wide
area on impact. Returned after
quest completion.

Name: Arkveld Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Arkveld scale.
Despite being incredibly dense
and hard, the edges chip easily.

Name: Arkveld Armorplate
Description:
A durable Arkveld carapace.
Named for how its scales
overlap like plate armor.

Name: White Arkveld Pelt
Description:
A white Arkveld pelt. Strong,
naturally twining strands create
extra protection against attacks.

Name: Arkveld Calloushell
Description:
A linked Arkveld carapace that
is connected by flexible sinew,
allowing it to move like a chain.

Name: Arkveld Horn+
Description:
A sharp, pointed Arkveld horn.
So menacing, its mere sight dispirits
any who must stand against it.

Name: Arkveld Gem
Description:
A mysterious gem that formed
inside an Arkveld. Its pulsating
white light seems to absorb life.

Name: Arkveld Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted an Arkveld.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Heavy Blunt Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that inflicts
massive blunt damage where
it lands.

Name: Heavy Slicing Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that inflicts
massive severing damage where
it lands.

Name: Heavy Explosion Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that explodes on
impact, causing massive damage.

Name: Basic Material
Description:
Assorted materials from target
monster obtained as bonus rewards.

Name: Valuable Material
Description:
Valuable materials from target
monster obtained as bonus rewards.

Name: Drearisite Scraps
Description:
Metal scraps manufactured in
Azuz. Can be used as a material
once smelted.

Name: Scarred Scale
Description:
A material found in the Iceshard
Cliffs. Despite its scarring, it
remains tough as any other scale.

Name: Ancient Wyvern Coin
Description:
A rarity found in the East. A
coin bearing a delicate etched
relief, long out of use.

Name: Heavy Piercing Pod
Description:
Slinger ammo that inflicts massive
piercing damage on impact.

Name: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_476
Description: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_EXP_476

Name: Chillshroom
Description:
This frosty mushroom is a
primary ingredient in cool
drinks.

Name: Hot Pepper
Description:
A plant spicy enough to set
your mouth on fire. Used for
making hot drinks.

Name: Ancient Weapon Fragment
Description:
Part of an ancient weapon.
Needs to be appraised.

Name: Nerscylla Shear
Description:
A flexible, venomous Nerscylla
fang. Beware its lethal poison
when handling it!

Name: Guardian Fulgur Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Guardian Fulgur
Anjanath scale. Surprisingly heavy,
and zaps you when touched.

Name: Guardian Fulgur Pelt+
Description:
A high-quality Guardian Fulgur
Anjanath pelt. Wild patterns have
overshadowed its original form.

Name: Guardian Fulgur Fang+
Description:
A sharp fang from a Guardian Fulgur
Anjanath. Built to withstand the
fierce crushing power of its jaw.

Name: Guardian Fulgur Nosebone+
Description:
The nasal bone of a Guardian
Fulgur Anjanath. The mucus from
it is charged with electricity.

Name: Guardian Fulgur Tail
Description:
A Guardian Fulgur Anjanath tail.
Packed with thick muscles that
help it maintain balance.

Name: Guardian Fulgur Gem
Description:
A rare jewel that developed within
a Guardian Fulgur Anjanath. Said
to hold the might of the heavens.

Name: Herbivore Carapace
Description:
A thick carapace from an
herbivore. Even the smallest
ones are incredibly durable.

Name: Bulaqchi Carapace
Description:
A high-quality Bulaqchi
carapace. Easy to process
and incredibly tough.

Name: Monster Fluid
Description:
A liquid bugs suck from
monsters. Mixes with insect
fluids to form an adhesive.

Name: Monster Broth
Description:
A broth made from only the
thickest of a monster's
juices. Quite rich.

Name: Talioth Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Talioth scale.
Built to survive fierce battles,
but still not much to look at.

Name: Wingdrake Hide+
Description:
A rare material carved from
wingdrakes. It's both tough and
easy to work with.

Name: Piragill Fin
Description:
A Piragill fin. Its sharp edge
cuts into prey like a knife
through butter.

Name: Piragill Fin+
Description:
A high-quality Piragill fin.
A deep scarlet, it will slice
flesh at the slightest touch.

Name: Kranodath Skull
Description:
A Kranodath skull. Its incredible
resilience makes it a great
material for armor.

Name: Kranodath Skull+
Description:
An extra hard Kranodath skull. So
tough that it won't crack even if
you pound on it with all your might.

Name: Comaqchi Shell
Description:
A Comaqchi shell. Incredibly
smooth with an attractive luster.

Name: Comaqchi Carapace
Description:
A high-quality Comaqchi shell.
Its glorious color bewitches all
those who see it.

Name: Guardian Seikret Feather
Description:
A Guardian Seikret feather.
Strong enough to deflect blades.

Name: Guardian Seikret Feather+
Description:
A high-quality Guardian Seikret
feather. Astoundingly lightweight,
yet perfectly resilient.

Name: Congalala Pelt
Description:
The pink fur of a Congalala.
The tufts of fluffy hair are an
ideal material for clothing.

Name: Congalala Claw
Description:
The long claw of a Congalala.
Large and sharp, it gouges
anything it touches.

Name: Congalala Fang
Description:
A Congalala incisor. While blunt,
it is tough enough to crush even
the hardest of substances.

Name: Vibrant Pelt
Description:
Vibrant hair that grows on the head
of a Congalala. The lovely colors
are proof of its position in its pack.

Name: Congalala Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Congalala.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Congalala Pelt+
Description:
High-quality Congalala fur. Stout
and resilient, an important
crafting material once processed.

Name: Congalala Claw+
Description:
A long, hard, sharp claw from the
wildest of Congalala, and no less
tricky to manage than its source.

Name: Congalala Fang+
Description:
An extra large Congalala fang.
Its sturdiness is better suited
for crushing than tearing.

Name: Vibrant Pelt+
Description:
Vibrant hair from a Congalala's head.
The tuft works as crown of sorts,
establishing its status as leader.

Name: Nerscylla Shell
Description:
The outer shell of a Nerscylla.
Extremely light, with a distinctly
aposematic coloration.

Name: Nerscylla Chelicera
Description:
The retractable venomous fang of
a Nerscylla. Handle with care!

Name: Nerscylla Claw
Description:
A lightweight, scythe-like claw
that enables the Nerscylla's
swift and deadly attacks.

Name: Nerscylla Spike
Description:
A dorsal spike and poison sac used
to drip poison onto prey passing
under the Nerscylla's nest.

Name: Nerscylla Certificate
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Nerscylla.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Nerscylla Carapace
Description:
A sturdy Nerscylla carapace. The
porcelain-white material is highly
prized, particularly among women.

Name: Nerscylla Claw+
Description:
This keen Nerscylla claw lashes
out from the shadows to claim
an ever-growing list of victims.

Name: Nerscylla Spike+
Description:
An especially large Nerscylla
spike, prized more for its lethal
poison sac than its sharpness.

Name: Nerscylla Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Nerscylla.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Kut-Ku Scale+
Description:
Quality scale from a Yian Kut-Ku.
Its size and weight make it even
more impressive than normal.

Name: Kut-Ku Carapace
Description:
Unyielding Yian Kut-Ku carapace.
Its vivid red hue won't dim even
when exposed to intense heat.

Name: Kut-Ku Ear
Description:
The distinctive ear of a Yian
Kut-Ku. Stretchy and resistant to
fire, it makes fine armor lining.

Name: Giant Beak
Description:
The massive beak of a Yian Kut-Ku.
Sturdy enough to peck through
even the rockiest of terrain.

Name: Kut-Ku Wing
Description:
Quality Yian Kut-Ku wing membrane.
A triple threat of sturdiness,
flexibility, and fire resistance.

Name: Yian Kut-Ku Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Yian
Kut-Ku. Used to make equipment.

Name: Rubbery Hide
Description:
Elastic, electricity-resistant hide
worn by a Nerscylla. Thought
to be from another monster.

Name: Rubbery Hide+
Description:
The quality hide of a Gypceros.
The baggy, stretchy feel of it is
oddly pleasing to the wearer.

Name: Gypceros Wing
Description:
A quality Gypceros wing membrane.
Offers the same shock and poison
protection—now with comfy stretch!

Name: Gypceros Head
Description:
The uniquely shaped head of
a Gypceros. A must-have for
Gypceros lovers!

Name: Gypceros Tail
Description:
The tail of a Gypceros. The most
pliant body part, and thus the
most difficult part to damage.

Name: Gypceros Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Gypceros.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Bird Wyvern Gem
Description:
A valuable gem that can be
harvested from bird wyverns. Said
to fetch a high price on the market.

Name: Dash Extract
Description:
A mysterious substance
culled from certain monsters
that increases endurance.

Name: Rathian Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Rathian.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Blangonga Pelt+
Description:
Fine fur from a Blangonga. Its
springy resilience and warmth
make it prized in cold regions.

Name: Blangonga Fang+
Description:
A Blangonga canine. As large
as a human thigh, it's
basically a weapon already.

Name: Blangonga Whisker
Description:
A glorious mustache is the
mark and pride of a Blangonga
leader, a symbol of its might.

Name: Blangonga Tail
Description:
The tail of a Blangonga.
The silky, lustrous coat
is heavenly to the touch.

Name: Blangonga Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Blangonga.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Gravios Carapace
Description:
The sturdy carapace of a Gravios.
Fused with ore by intense heat,
it has grown abnormally tough.

Name: Gravios Skull
Description:
The head armor of a Gravios,
hardened by its own heat.
Makes it hard to work with, too.

Name: Gravios Pleura+
Description:
Shell that covers a Gravios's torso.
It's grown so thick over time that
average attacks do nothing to it.

Name: Gravios Medulla
Description:
Though hard to extract and hard
to craft, the brain stem is an
especially precious Gravios part.

Name: Gravios Wing
Description:
The hefty wing of a Gravios.
Recently, the demand and value
of the material has been rising.

Name: Gravios Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Gravios.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Rathalos Scale+
Description:
An extraordinarily durable
scale carved from the body
of a Rathalos.

Name: Rathalos Carapace
Description:
This Rathalos carapace emanates
a nobility befitting the King
of the Skies.

Name: Rathalos Wing
Description:
The wing of a Rathalos.
Skilled artisans can craft
it into strong equipment.

Name: Rathalos Tail
Description:
A severed Rathalos tail covered
in plates and keen spines. It has
any number of uses.

Name: Rathalos Ruby
Description:
A rare, precious gem
from inside a Rathalos.
Almost too nice to use.

Name: Rathalos Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Rathalos.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Gore Magala Scale+
Description:
A deep black scale that seems
to devour surrounding light,
not reflect it.

Name: Gore Magala Carapace
Description:
The Gore Magala's handsome
black suit of armor, said to
negate all blows.

Name: Gore Magala Wing+
Description:
A horrifying wing that casts
a hungry shadow over prey
and drives them insane.

Name: Gore Magala Ripclaw+
Description:
A claw from a Gore Magala's
second foreleg. It inflicts Frenzy
and generations of suffering.

Name: Gore Magala Tail
Description:
A pliant tail covered in
reverse scales that strikes
like a whip, not a blade.

Name: Gore Magala Feeler+
Description:
A well-honed sensory organ from
a Gore Magala that oozes violet
melancholy from its infected tip.

Name: Gore Magala Nyctgem
Description:
A pure, jet-black jewel that
imprisons and swallows all
nearby light.

Name: Gore Magala Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Gore
Magala. Used to make equipment.

Name: Frenzy Crystal
Description:
An unsettling crystal wreathed
in Frenzied power. Handle with
extreme care.

Name: Conga Pelt
Description:
A Conga pelt. Sturdy and soft
to the touch but must be
deodorized before it's processed.

Name: Conga Pelt+
Description:
A high-quality Conga pelt. The
thick fur can be used to make
long-lasting equipment.

Name: Vespoid Shell
Description:
A Vespoid shell. If processed
correctly, it can become just
as tough as a wyvern's hide.

Name: Vespoid Carapace
Description:
The hard carapace of a Vespoid.
It takes on a unique quality
once processed.

Name: Vespoid Wing
Description:
The wing of a Vespoid. Extremely
difficult to process and produces
widely varying results.

Name: Vespoid Innerwing
Description:
The innerwing of a Vespoid.
Sharp and elegant, like a blade.

Name: Blango Pelt+
Description:
A high-quality Blango pelt.
Difficult to process, but
valuable nonetheless.

Name: Lightcrystal
Description:
A precious and extremely hard
substance with a faint glow.
Sometimes used for crafting tools.

Name: Novacrystal
Description:
High quality Lightcrystal. Highly
coveted for its rarity, it's used for
only the finest of metalworking.

Name: Firestone
Description:
Ore that is scorching even at
room temperature. Its heat can
be used to fuse materials.

Name: Firecell Stone
Description:
A magma-like deposit that only
trained hands can handle. Armor
made from it is first-class.

Name: Fucium Ore
Description:
A mysterious metal found in the
Ruins of Wyveria, capable of fusing
any other materials together.

Name: Icium
Description:
Precious metal from the Iceshard
Cliffs. Shines bright white when
the light catches it.

Name: Guardian Fulgur Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Guardian Fulgur
Anjanath. Used to make equipment.

Name: Congalala Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted a Congalala.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Charred Oilbone
Description:
A bone found in the Oilwell Basin.
Covered in a thick coat of oil that
built up over many years.

Name: Frozen Icebone
Description:
A bone found in the Iceshard
Cliffs. Tempered over millennia
deep within the frozen earth.

Name: Tough Guardian Bone
Description:
A bone found in the Ruins of
Wyveria. Its peculiar shape
is unique to the local wildlife.

Name: Quality Bone
Description:
A bone used as crafting material.
Its ease of use and hardness allow
it to be shaped into better gear.

Name: Crushed Crystal
Description:
A shard of crystal carved from the
carcass of a Guardian. Can be used
as a melding material.

Name: Cloudy Crystal
Description:
A hazy crystal carved from the
carcass of a Guardian. Can be
used as a melding material.

Name: Coruscating Crystal
Description:
A glittering crystal carved from
the carcass of a Guardian. Can
be used as a melding material.

Name: Flame Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
flammable powder. Handle
with extreme care.

Name: Inferno Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
powder that ignites if it so
much as touches air. Danger!

Name: Aqua Sac
Description:
A monster organ designed to hold
and preserve water.

Name: Torrent Sac
Description:
A monster organ designed to
hold and preserve copious
amounts of water.

Name: Thunder Sac
Description:
A monster organ that can
store up large amounts of
high voltage electricity.

Name: Frost Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
extremely cold fluid. Handle
with care.

Name: Freezer Sac
Description:
A monster organ with
tremendous chilling power.
Flash-freezes its surroundings.

Name: Poison Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
a lethal toxin. Handle with
extreme care.

Name: Toxin Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
an extremely potent toxin.
Even one touch can be risky.

Name: Lala Barina Mucus
Description:
Body fluid from a Lala Barina.
A sticky, red liquid that causes
paralysis.

Name: Lala Barina Mucus+
Description:
Thick body fluid from a Lala Barina.
As red as fresh blood, it contains
a powerful paralytic.

Name: Sleep Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
a knockout powder capable
of inducing sleep.

Name: Coma Sac
Description:
A monster organ filled with
a dangerous powder. One whiff
can induce a coma.

Name: Guardian Blood
Description:
Guardian blood containing an
unknown substance. A valuable
research material.

Name: Guardian Blood+
Description:
Guardian blood with rather
peculiar properties. Requires
further research.

Name: Great Hibiscus
Description:
A large, brightly colored flower
found in the Ruins of Wyveria.
Spreads its seeds through the air.

Name: Dalthydon Wool
Description:
A product of Kunafa. Perfectly
suited for desert life. Try
bringing it to the Smithy.

Name: Azuz Tanned Leather
Description:
A product of Azuz. The leather
is repeatedly repaired for extended
use. Try taking it to the Smithy.

Name: Suja Textiles
Description:
A product of Suja. Its unique pattern
has roots in Wyverian tradition.
Try taking it to the Smithy.

Name: Sild Cotton
Description:
A product of Sild. A high-quality
material that can be used as-is.
Try bringing it to the Smithy.

Name: Gajau Hide
Description:
The hide of a Gajau. Covered in
a thick slime that grants water
resistance.

Name: Speartuna Fin
Description:
The sharp fin of a Speartuna.
Might be useful for something
if you bring it to the Smithy.

Name: Commission Ticket
Description:
A ticket in the image of a hunter
who traveled to the New World.
Try taking it to the Smithy.

Name: Mimiphyta Ticket
Description:
A ticket depicting the ecology
of Mimiphyta. Give it to the
Smithy to get special equipment.

Name: Mystery Orb - Sword
Description:
A sphere with faint power that
is revealed through appraisal.
Becomes an offensive decoration.

Name: Glowing Orb - Sword
Description:
A sphere with hidden power that
can be revealed through appraisal.
Becomes an offensive decoration.

Name: Ancient Orb - Sword
Description:
A sphere with incredible power that
can be revealed through appraisal.
Becomes an offensive decoration.

Name: Armor Sphere
Description:
Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse
this to armor to improve it by
a tiny amount.

Name: Armor Sphere+
Description:
Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse
this to armor to improve it by
a small amount.

Name: Advanced Armor Sphere
Description:
Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse
this to armor to improve it.

Name: Hard Armor Sphere
Description:
A rigid, high-density armor
sphere. Fuse this to armor to
improve it by a great amount.

Name: Rocksteady Mantle
Description:
Negates damage reactions, protects
hearing, grants wind and tremor
resistance, and reduces damage.

Name: Mending Mantle
Description:
Steadily restores health over a set
amount of time.

Name: Evasion Mantle
Description:
Upon just evading a blow, triggers
a special evasive maneuver that
boosts attack and alters combos.

Name: Corrupted Mantle
Description:
Decreases health, but raises affinity
and weapon stats. Attack and affinity
further increased in certain conditions.

Name: Wyvern Egg
Description:
A flying wyvern's egg. Deliver
it back to camp...if you can.

Name: Charred Lizard
Description:
A lizard charred crispy by Wudwuds.
Removes all traces of poison and
restores both health and stamina.

Name: Wild Jerky
Description:
Dried meat beloved for its wild
flavor and toughness. Increases
natural healing and cures bleeding.

Name: Catalyst
Description:
Works with other materials to
enhance their effects. Cannot
be used by itself.

Name: Gunpowder
Description:
A dangerous substance that
explodes when struck or heated.
Used in Large Barrel Bombs.

Name: Small Barrel
Description:
A small, empty barrel.
Combine with fire herbs
to make it into a bomb.

Name: Large Barrel
Description:
A large, empty barrel.
Combine with gunpowder
to make it into a bomb.

Name: Spider Web
Description:
A very sticky web. Used
to craft pitfall traps.

Name: Net
Description:
A sturdy net that supports a certain
amount of weight without breaking.
Perfect for pitfall traps.

Name: Gunpowderfish Scale
Description:
A Gunpowderfish scale. Combine
with a large barrel bomb to
dramatically increase its firepower.

Name: Burst Arowana Scale
Description:
A Burst Arowana scale. Combine
with Normal Ammo to make a
large amount of Slicing Ammo.

Name: Bomb Arowana Scale
Description:
A Bomb Arowana scale. Combine
with Normal Ammo to make a
large amount of Sticky Ammo.

Name: Gilded Scale
Description:
A Goldenfry scale. Used by
artisans in their crafts.

Name: Golden Scale
Description:
A Goldenfish scale. They shimmer
like only pure gold can.

Name: Platinum Scale
Description:
A Platinumfish scale. They give
off a beautiful gleam.

Name: Pick-a-meal Voucher
Description:
Exchange this voucher in the
Grand Hub Canteen for one order
of your favorite regional meal.

Name: Steel Melding Ticket
Description:
A ticket used by Wyverians. Hand
it over when melding decorations
to get a slight discount.

Name: Silver Melding Ticket
Description:
A ticket used by Wyverians. Hand
it over when melding decorations
to get a discount.

Name: Steel Relic Ticket
Description:
A ticket used by Wyverians. Hand
it over when melding relics to
get a slight discount.

Name: Silver Relic Ticket
Description:
A ticket used by Wyverians. Hand
it over when melding relics to
get a discount.

Name: Steel Egg
Description:
An egg of glittering steel.
Rare but useless to hunters.
Sells for a good price.

Name: Silver Egg
Description:
An egg of glittering silver.
Rare but useless to hunters.
Sells for a very good price.

Name: Golden Egg
Description:
An egg of glittering gold.
Valuable but useless to hunters.
Sells for a fortune.

Name: Heavy Armor Sphere
Description:
A solid, high-density armor
sphere. Fuse this to armor to
improve it by a vast amount.

Name: Monster Keenbone
Description:
Bone obtained from high-rank large
monsters. It has a razor sharp tip
that retains its strength after forging.

Name: Monster Hardbone
Description:
Precious bone obtained from high
rank large monsters. Their rarity
makes them highly sought after.

Name: Stoutbone
Description:
The bone of a large, high
ranking monster. Very sturdy.

Name: Great Stoutbone
Description:
The bone of a large, high
ranking monster. Extremely
solid and durable.

Name: Hunter Symbol I
Description:
Proof that you've hunted
a tempered monster, certifying
your strength.

Name: Hunter Symbol II
Description:
Proof that you've hunted
a fierce tempered monster,
certifying your fearlessness.

Name: Hunter Symbol III
Description:
Proof that you've hunted
a vicious tempered monster,
certifying your heroism.

Name: Gold Melding Ticket
Description:
A ticket used by Wyverians. Hand
it over when melding decorations
to get a great discount.

Name: Gold Relic Ticket
Description:
A ticket used by Wyverians. Hand
it over when melding relics to
get a great discount.

Name: Guardian Pelt
Description:
Contains an unknown substance.
It has lost any color it previously
had and courses with energy.

Name: Guardian Pelt+
Description:
A high-quality Guardian pelt.
Exceptionally smooth and tough.

Name: Drearisite
Description:
A mysterious material smelted in
Azuz. Has been used to make
equipment since ancient times.

Name: Specklite
Description:
A mysterious material smelted
in Azuz. Not as pure as it could
be, but still of impeccable quality.

Name: Argecite
Description:
A mysterious material smelted
in Azuz. It's apparently primarily
used in high-quality equipment.

Name: Oricalcite
Description:
A mysterious, high-quality material
smelted in Azuz. Equipment made
from it is second to none.

Name: Common Wood Minnow
Description:
A common wooden lure shaped
like a small fish. Good for any
kind of fish.

Name: Golden Bughead
Description:
A lure that looks like a shining
beetle. Good for catching gaudy
fish, like Goldenfish.

Name: Emerald Jitterbait
Description:
A lure with a blade made of ore.
Good for catching useful fish,
like Sushifish.

Name: Tuff Joint Bait
Description:
A lure shaped like a Cephalos.
Good for catching large, swift
fish, like Gastronome Tuna.

Name: Duster Rig
Description:
A lure shaped like a Starduster.
Good for catching fish that like
dark or muddy places, like Gajau.

Name: Tentacle Jig
Description:
A lure made with thorngrass.
Good for catching aquatic creatures
that have tentacles or feelers.

Name: Close-range Coating
Description:
A coating designed to deal more
damage to nearby targets, at the
cost of a reduced maximum range.

Name: Power Coating
Description:
A coating that increases
the attack power of arrows.

Name: Pierce Coating
Description:
A coating that increases piercing
ability. Depending on the monster,
it can deal multiple hits.

Name: Paralysis Coating
Description:
A coating that applies paralysis
effects to arrows.

Name: Poison Coating
Description:
A coating that applies poison
effects to arrows.

Name: Sleep Coating
Description:
A coating that applies sleep
effects to arrows.

Name: Blast Coating
Description:
A coating that applies explosive
powder to arrows.

Name: Exhaust Coating
Description:
A coating that applies a fluid
which induces exhaust to arrows.

Name: Whetfish Fin+
Description:
A fish fin used to sharpen weapons.
Works better than a whetstone
and can be reused if you're lucky.

Name: Great Sushifish Scale
Description:
Scale from a Sushifish.
Eat to get a large health/natural
healing boost or to treat bleeding.

Name: Old Weapon Shard - Blade
Description:
A piece of a discarded, old
blade. Needs to be appraised.

Name: Old Weapon Shard - Tube
Description:
A cylindrical part of an old weapon
that's been thrown away. Needs to
be appraised.

Name: Old Weapon Shard - Disc
Description:
A disc-like part of an old weapon
that's been thrown away. Needs to
be appraised.

Name: Old Weapon Shard - Device
Description:
A part of an old weapon that has
some sort of device on it. Needs to
be appraised.

Name: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_690
Description: <COLOR FF0000>#Rejected#</COLOR> Item_IT_EXP_690

Name: Gracium
Description:
Precious ore from the Iceshard Cliffs.
Swathed in frigid air that shines pale
blue when the light catches it.

Name: Wyverian Bloodstone Shard
Description:
Obtained from destroying a tempered
wound. Has a deep sanguine hue.
Can be used as a melding material.

Name: Wyverian Bloodstone (S)
Description:
Obtained from destroying a tempered
wound. Has a deep sanguine hue.
Can be used as a melding material.

Name: Wyverian Bloodstone
Description:
Obtained from destroying a tempered
wound. Has a deep sanguine hue.
Can be used as a melding material.

Name: Wyverian Bloodstone (L)
Description:
Obtained from destroying a tempered
wound. Larger than most of its type.
Can be used as a melding material.

Name: Wyverian Bloodstone Chunk
Description:
Obtained from destroying a tempered
wound. One of the largest of its kind.
Can be used as a melding material.

Name: Balahara Black Pearl
Description:
A jewel formed from ore that
spent years inside a Balahara.
Bewitchingly beautiful.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Ruby
Description:
A rare jewel that developed in
a Guardian Rathalos' body. Said
to wield the power of an inferno.

Name: Guardian Rathalos Plate
Description:
A plate from a Guardian Rathalos.
Strengthened by the flow of energy,
its inherent heat blazes forth.

Name: Jin Dahaad Tail
Description:
The tail of a Jin Dahaad. Has a
cooling organ that continues to
make cold air even when severed.

Name: Expedition Headgear Ticket
Description:
A ticket inscribed with the emblem
of the expedition. Give it to the
Smithy to get special equipment.

Name: Zoh Shia Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to
those who have hunted Zoh
Shia. Used to make equipment.

Name: Zoh Shia Crystalscale
Description:
A crystallized Zoh Shia scale.
Its dull glow evinces the great
energy it contains.

Name: Zoh Shia Layershell
Description:
The coiled nature of Zoh Shia's
layered shell looks as though it
protects as much as it constricts.

Name: Zoh Shia Stakeclaw
Description:
Stake-like Zoh Shia claws extended
by hardened Wylk. The Wylkrystal
growths are eerily uniform.

Name: Zoh Shia Crystalhorn
Description:
A crystal-coated Zoh Shia horn.
Heavy and wedge-like, as though
it were used to seal something.

Name: Zoh Shia Crystaltail
Description:
A crystal-covered Zoh Shia tail.
The crystals continue to grow
even after the tail is severed.

Name: Faux Whitegleam Orb
Description:
An inorganic orb from inside Zoh
Shia. Something wriggles deep
within its elaborate design.

Name: Blackember Mass
Description:
A small, swollen mass from the
inside of Zoh Shia. It pulses
with an alien-like quality.

Name: Mizutsune Certificate S
Description:
A Guild certificate awarded to those
who have hunted a Mizutsune.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Mizutsune Scale+
Description:
A high-quality Mizutsune scale.
Older scales polished over
time can be very valuable.

Name: Mizutsune Purplefur+
Description:
High-quality purple Mizutsune
fur. More foam-absorbent than
its lighter counterpart.

Name: Mizutsune Claw+
Description:
Friction-reducing bubblefoam
helps this deadly claw slice
through prey like sushi.

Name: Mizutsune Fin+
Description:
A high-quality Mizutsune fin.
Bubblefoam gives it an elegant
pattern prettier than dye.

Name: Mizutsune Tail
Description:
A flowing Mizutsune tail.
It's prized for its supple
fur and beautiful scales.

Name: Bubblefoam+
Description:
The top layer of Mizutsune
fluid. Removes impurities
and is used in many rituals.

Name: Mizutsune Water Orb
Description:
A multicolored orb formed
from a crystalized Mizutsune
scale and bubblefoam.

Name: Rey Dau Certificate γ
Description:
A Guild certificate for hunting
an Arch-tempered Rey Dau.
Used to make equipment.

Name: Blossomdance Ticket
Description:
A ticket you receive for attending
the Blossomdance. Can be
exchanged for festive equipment.

Name: Blossom Ticket
Description:
A ticket depicting a flowery set
of armor. Give it to the Smithy
to get special equipment.

Name: Blossomdance Catalog
Description:
A ticket depicting elegant
decorations. Give it to the
Smithy to get special equipment.

Name: Chata Coin
Description:
A coin given to those who
have bested a Chatacabra
in the Arena.

Name: Rathian Coin
Description:
A coin given to those who
have bested a Rathian in
the Arena.

Name: Barrel Bowling Voucher
Description:
A voucher for a chance to play
a Grand Hub mini-game. Has
a whimsical DIY look.

Name: Blossomdance Voucher
Description:
A voucher usable only during
the Blossomdance. Exchange
it for a festive meal.

Name: Amstrigian Ticket
Description:
A ticket depicting the ecology
of Amstrigian. Give it to the
Smithy to get special equipment.

Name: Sealed Dragon Cloth
Description:
A cloth used to seal the corpse
of a dreaded elder dragon. Truth
or lie, the ominousness is palatable.

Name: Blossom Barrel Bomb
Description:
A large barrel bomb from the
Blossomdance. Explodes with
a flurry of flower petals.

Name: Pinnacle Coin
Description:
A commemorative coin bestowed on
hunters who have mastered the craft.
The value of its sheen? Priceless.

Name: Kunafa Meal Voucher
Description:
Exchange this voucher in the
Grand Hub Canteen for one order
of the Kunafa regional meal.

Name: Azuz Meal Voucher
Description:
Exchange this voucher in the
Grand Hub Canteen for one order
of the Azuz regional meal.

Name: Sild Meal Voucher
Description:
Exchange this voucher in the
Grand Hub Canteen for one order
of the Sild regional meal.

Name: Suja Meal Voucher
Description:
Exchange this voucher in the
Grand Hub Canteen for one order
of the Suja regional meal.
